name: ELEX WooCommerce Australia Post Shipping
author: ELEXtensions

sections.description:
ELEX WooCommerce Australia Post Shipping plugin automates your shipping process by fetching the shipping rates ( Domestic & International ) using Australia Post APIs. Based on the shipping destination location and properties of the items added to the cart, eligible Australia Post services will be fetched & displayed on the Cart and Checkout page. Customers can choose the desired service and proceed with the checkout.

Integrates WooCommerce to Australia Post

Once ELEX WooCommerce Australia Post Shipping plugin is installed and configured with the necessary information (please visit the installation section for more info), your WordPress/WooCommerce Shop will be ready to ship using Australia Post. This plugin will add the Australia Post shipping method as one of the shipping methods in WooCommerce. The Basic plugin works for both contracted and non-contracted accounts.

Top Features

  • Access Australia Post Real-time Rates
  • Choose AusPost non-contracted account or eParcel contracted account
  • Show cheapest rates to Customers
  • Combined Export
  • Offer Australia Post services to only specific countries

Australia Post Services

Plugin Supports both Domestic and International DHL Express Services. Few of those services are listed below.
* EXPRESS NATIONAL FULL RATE
* NATIONAL FULL RATE
* INTL ECONOMY W SOD/ REGD POST
* INTL STANDARD/PACK & TRACK
* INTL EXPRESS MERCH/ECI MERCH
* INTL ECONOMY/AIRMAIL PARCELS
* PARCEL POST + SIGNATURE
* EXPRESS POST + SIGNATURE

Premium version – Real-time Rates and Label Printing

ELEX WooCommerce Australia Post Shipping – Premium Version Features

  • Print Shipping Label with Postage.
  • Supports Australia Post eParcel and Australia Post StarTrack Service.
  • Australia Post MyPost – Rates & Print Shipping Labels powerd by ReachShip Multi-Carrier Shipping Platform
  • Estimated Delivery Date.
  • Print eParcel Shipping Label (for Contracted Rates).
  • eParcel International Shipping Documents.
  • Australia Post Order Summary / Manifest.
  • Box packing – Pack the items in the cart to configured boxes.
  • Weight-Based Packing.
  • Price Adjustment for Each Shipping Service.
  • Customization Option for Each Service Name.
  • Service Level Signature/Registered Options.
  • Service Level Extra Cover Charges.
  • Australia Post Shipment Tracking.
  • Timely compatibility updates and bug fixes.
  • Premium support!

Upgrade to Premium!

About ELEXtensions

We are a group of WordPress and WooCommerce enthusiasts with a vision to solve genuine problems related to WordPress & WooCommerce stores.

About Australia Post

Australia Post, formally the Australian Postal Corporation, is the government business enterprise that provides postal services in Australia. It operates in three core areas: letters and associated services; retail merchandise and agency services; and parcels and logistics. Australia Post operates regular mail delivery as well as an express/courier service through Messenger Post (Now trading as Startrack Courier). Australia post also has an optional service called MyPost where you can create an account and manage your delivery.
sections.installation:
1. Upload the plugin folder to the /wp-content/plugins/ directory.
  2. Activate the plugin through the Plugins menu in WordPress.
  3. Thats it! you can now configure the plugin.
sections.faq:
Is the plugin configuration complicated?

The plugin is very easy to configure. The documentation includes a step-by-step tutorial, FAQs, Troubleshooting Guide, Knowledge Base and Code snippets.

sections.reviews:
This is the one to get for Australia Post

By robaxxx on March 18, 2024

Have had the paid version for a year and no issues. When we did need help with something I was happy to find that the support is quick and willing.

I initially chose this one because the free version provides international shipping rates. However, combined shipping/packaging does require the full version.

Has lots of other features we aren't using, but am happy to have them in case we do. Nice plugin overall.

Excellent support

By dvadlamoodi on March 2, 2024


I've been collaborating with ElExtensions for about a month now. Whenever an issue arises, the team promptly joins a call to address it. Their thorough analysis is instrumental in pinpointing the root cause of any problems. They patiently guide me through each step in case the plugin encounters any failures. I'm delighted to continue working with ElExtensions.

Initially, my plugin faced limitations due to the absence of a StarTrack premium business account with Australia Post. However, ElExtensions provided invaluable support by offering alternative solutions, demonstrating remarkable patience in answering all my inquiries. I'm grateful for the prompt and patient assistance from the Australia Post product manager. My sincere thanks to her and the entire team.

Super frustrated - but now happy

By jimmiechua on March 6, 2024

Have tried to get this to work since September last year. Have spent 60+ hours on phone calls/Google Meets with Elextensions and Australia Post IT support. On one ocassion burned a whole day to find out there servers were down. There are two key issues:

  1. The Australian Eastern Seaboard time zone does not match up with their support at all. 4.30pm is the ONLY time available between business hours here so you often have to wait days before you can get a time slot that works unless you are happy to book a time at 1 am.
  2. We cannot get a price through the API if a product has a dimension smaller than 15cm*15cm*15cm??

06/03/24 - update
Met with the team again and this time they walked through the configuration via a screen share and were able to advise that in order to get a postage price through the API for items smaller than 15*15*15cm we needed to have flat rates enabled. The team also wrote some code, added that to the plug in and sent me a zip to reinstall the plug in and guess what?? After 6 months we finally have it working!!! Thank you team Elex.

Paid version works well

By katmacau on February 19, 2024

Have been using the paid version of this plugin on numerous woocommerce sites. Any issues I've had the Elex team have been able to provide support on.

Some features are only available to 'contracted' AusPost clients. Small time business may not have this type of account with AusPost so wont get access to those advanced features. Thats an AusPost thing and not an Elex thing.

Recommend this product for AusPost shipping calculator.

Does a great job

By xcitebikes on November 29, 2023

Plugin covers all our needs regarding Australia Post options. We use many of the possible customizations, like discount for some options, we renamed a few others, and charge handling fees for others. Very happy with product.

Best plugin for Auspost API integration.

By wpsubash on November 3, 2023

I had to use the premium version and it was completely worth it. Also, the after-sales service is top-notch, had a few issues and confusion but they helped me fix it quickly. Thanks a lot. 

Free Version doesnt work

By DA42 (troyw2015) on May 4, 2023

Installed the free version, added the API, followed instructions, but the instructions do not apply to the free version and none of the set up features are available. Even with the limited set up boxes ticked and API added, there is no Shipping Method available in the Shipping zones and certainly nothing in the front end. I'm sure the paid version works but the free version does not.

Top Rated Plugin & Exceptional After-Sales Service!!

By EWD (surfshak) on February 22, 2023

As a digital marketing agency, we have worked with numerous WooCommerce plugins and shipping solutions over the years...so we can confidently say that the ELEX WooCommerce Australia Post Shipping plugin is one of the best carrier integration plugins we have used.

Firstly, the plugin's functionality is unparalleled. It has been exceptionally well architectured; integrates seamlessly between Aus Post/eParcel and WooCommerce; and provides accurate and up-to-date live shipping rates; labelling; parcel packaging; tracking; and more from Australia Post [Premium Version]. This in turn allows our clients to provide their customers with a reliable and efficient automated shipping solution within their ecommerce stores.

The plugin is also easy to use, with an intuitive interface that even the least tech-savvy website owners can navigate.

However, what truly sets ELEX apart from other plugin developers is the after-sales service provided by Dixit and ELEX's team of developers. We have been using their numerous shipping plugins for several years now, and they are ALWAYS quick to respond to any queries or concerns we may have. They go above and beyond to ensure that any issues are resolved as quickly as possible.

Furthermore, we have been impressed with the developers' willingness to accommodate a number of customizations when needed. They are always happy to work with us to ensure that the plugin meets our clients' specific needs, which we find is a level of service that is rare in today's digital landscape.

Overall, we cannot recommend the ELEX WooCommerce Australia Post Shipping plugin highly enough. The plugin's functionality is outstanding, and the after-sales service provided by the developers is exceptional. If you are looking for a reliable and efficient shipping solution in Australia for your WooCommerce store, look no further than this plugin. EWD Agency, Australia.
